Class Merge<R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bakdata.dedupe.fusion.Merge<R>
  • Type Parameters:
    R - the type of the record.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConflictResolution<R,​R>
    public final class Merge<R>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ConflictResolution<R,​R>
    A nested conflict resolution for complex types.

    The individual elements are resolved with specific ConflictResolution functions and then a new instance of the record type is created with the respective values.

    If any exception during fusion occurs, the following field resolutions are still applied and a joint FusionException is thrown.

    See Also:
    CommonConflictResolutions.merge(Class), CommonConflictResolutions.merge(Supplier)

                                                                                    @NonNull
                                                                                    @NonNull FusionContext context)
        Description copied from interface: ConflictResolution
        Tries the best to resolve the value but may end up with multiple concurrent values.

        For example, if two values "a" and "b" with equal weight remain after prior resolution, this method returns a list of both.

        The return value should be treated as a bag; that is, the order of the values does not matter.

        Specified by:
        resolveNonEmptyPartially in interface ConflictResolution<R,​R>
        Parameters:
        annotatedValues - the non-empty, unresolved values.
        context - a fusion context with additional configurations.
        Returns:
        the resolved values in a best-effort approach.
